The paper deals with action recognition in videos using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks to learn representations for action recognition also falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of optical flow vector fields, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of high-quality optical flow estimation, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or neural engineering (cs.NE).
